Overview:
This project focuses on analyzing Instagram fan sentiment for the New York Yankees to uncover actionable insights for content strategy, fan engagement, and brand positioning.

Unlike traditional sentiment analysis, this approach goes beyond polarity (positive/negative) and integrates emotion detection, engagement weighting, and business-driven segmentation to translate fan conversations into strategic decisions.

Objective:
To transform unstructured Instagram comment data into clear, actionable insights that can guide:
- Content strategy
- Fan engagement initiatives
- Brand and player positioning
- Revenue linked decision making

Key Approach: 
1. Data Collection
Scraped Instagram comments using Apify
Focused on Yankees-related posts (players, rivals, brand moments, events)
Dataset includes comment text, timestamps, engagement signals

2. Sentiment Modeling
Baseline Model
Implemented VADER for initial polarity classification
Advanced Modeling
Applied RoBERTa (transformer-based model) for deeper contextual sentiment

Improved handling of:
sarcasm
emotional nuance
sports-specific language
Custom Enhancements
Post-context boosting
Adjusts neutral comments based on overall post sentiment
Sports lexicon tuning
Accounts for domain-specific phrases (e.g., “we’re cooked”, “that’s tough”)
Emoji sentiment integration

3. Emotion Classification
Mapped comments into business relevant emotional categories:

Joy
Frustration
Excitement
Pride
Disappointment
Neutral

This enables a more granular understanding of fan reactions beyond polarity.

4. Business-Themed Segmentation
Comments were grouped into strategic themes:

Player performance
Brand identity
Rivalries
Fan community
Pricing/value perception
Experience & atmosphere

This allows direct linkage between sentiment and business levers.

5. Engagement-Weighted Insights
Not all comments are equal.

High-engagement posts were weighted more heavily
Enables prioritization of what actually drives fan interaction, not just volume
